						               													<description>It's a last-minute costume party among friends, and everyone is rushing to the nearest costume shop. Each person is trying to gather the pieces of their choice before ducking into the fitting room. Let the party begin!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;GOAL OF THE GAME&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Find all parts for the most costumes in order to accumulate the most points (buttons) after four rounds. A complete costume comprises three cards (costume + headdress + accessory) or a single card for the bumblebee, bunny, and sumo.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;HOW TO PLAY?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The players count together, &amp;quot;1,2,3&amp;quot; and simultaneously reveal the top card from their stacks, and place it face-up on the table.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If there are no complete costumes visible amongst all the cards, everyone count &amp;quot;1,2,3&amp;quot; and flips a new card, placing it beside the cards already visible. Thus, the number of cards visible gradually increases.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As soon you see a complete costume, tap the bell, and announce the name of the costume you saw. If your answer is correct, you take the three cards that compose this costume, and place them face-up in front of you.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the end of each round, you earn one button per costume you collected.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Whoever has the most buttons at the end of the fourth round wins!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
